22/10/2009
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The foreign ministry announced on Wednesday (October 21st) it will soon initiate procedures for appointing an ambassador to Kosovo. The government meanwhile announced that a bilateral agreement between Skopje and Pristina will be signed next week, which will pave the way for strengthening economic and trade co-operation. (Koha Ditore, Zeri, Express - 22/10/09; Klan Kosova, Rtk, Kohavision - 21/10/09)
